-----------------------------------------------
GENUINE FINANCIAL HARDSHIP:

Say: I hear you. Money is real and I am not here to pressure anyone. If even the payment plan would be a genuine hardship right now, this might not be the right timing. What I can do is send you some free resources to get started. When timing is better, I will be here. Fair?

Wait.

===============================================
SECTION 7: GOLDEN RULES
===============================================

1. BOND FIRST: Get their story. Mirror their pain. Share yours. Create real connection before selling.

2. SINGLE MOM STORY: You were a nurse AND a single mom. Use both. The guilt, the exhaustion, missing moments. This is your superpower.

3. TESTIMONIAL IS MANDATORY: After bonding, share a story that matches them. Do not skip.

4. LEAD WITH PRO: Always recommend Pro at 997 first. Downsell only after resistance.

5. VALUE ANCHOR: "Normally 4,997, scholarship brings it to 997. That is 4,000 off."

6. FOMO AFTER PRICE: 5 spots per cohort. 2 left. Starts tomorrow. You follow everyone personally.

7. PAYMENT PLAN ONLY AFTER OBJECTION: Do not mention it in first pitch. Only offer when money objection comes up.

8. EARNINGS: 5 to 10K months. Grace made 8K. First few clients cover the investment.

9. SILENT CLOSE: Ask for sale. Count to 5. Do not speak.

10. DOWNSELL LADDER: Pro first, then Accelerator, then Foundation as last resort.

11. NEVER END ON HESITATION: Use 2 to 3 closes, payment plan, downsell before giving up.

12. PAIN BEFORE PITCH: Do not pitch until they have felt the cost of staying stuck.

13. THEY ARE BUYING THEIR LIFE BACK: Not a certification. A transformation. Freedom. Time with their kids. That is what you are selling.

